  <section>
    <h2>SoRSS — Soft Gastric Simulator</h2>
    <p><em>Hashem, R. et al. — Soft Robotics (2022)</em></p>

    <p>Short summary: a soft, anatomically inspired gastric simulator designed to emulate stomach anatomy and motility for device testing and training.</p>

    <ul>
      <li><strong>Problem:</strong> Lack of realistic, repeatable gastric phantoms for device validation and training.</li>
      <li><strong>Approach:</strong> Design and build a soft, ring-shaped simulator with controllable motility and embedded sensing to emulate antral contractions.</li>
      <li><strong>Outcome:</strong> A validated soft simulator used for closed-loop control experiments and early-stage device testing.</li>
      <li><strong>Materials & methods:</strong> Soft pneumatic actuators, embedded sensors, benchtop testing and closed-loop control experiments.</li>
      <li><strong>Links:</strong> <a href="/publications.html">Publication list</a> • <a href="https://scholar.google.com/citations?user=YcmYPOwAAAAJ" target="_blank">Google Scholar</a></li>
    </ul>

